-- Arcapita Said to Hire Advisers for $1.1 Billion Loan Repayment
-- B y   S t e f a n i a   B i a n c h i   a n d   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2012-02-27T13:14:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-27/arcapita-said-to-hire-advisers-for-1-1-billion-loan-repayment.html
Arcapita Bank BSC, owners of Irish
power utility Viridian Group Plc, hired NM Rothschild & Sons
Ltd.,  KPMG  and Linklaters LLP to advise on a $1.1 billion loan
repayment due in March, said two people familiar with the plans.  Royal Bank of Scotland Plc  is chairing a coordinating
committee of lenders, one of the people said. They declined to
be identified because the matter is private.  A spokesmen for Arcapita declined to comment. Nicole Hayde,
a spokeswoman for RBS in Dubai, didnâ€™t have a comment when
contacted today. The Financial Times reported the appointment
